<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-654-716  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 654 716.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Simulation  July 1990 v55 n1 p17(7).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FAWSIM: a flexible artificial workload simulator for Unix systems.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brown, Terrance J.; Shub, Charles M.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>This paper describes a flexible artificial workload simulator inuse both as a pedagogic aid in a teaching environment and as atool in a software prototype test facility.andP;  The backgroundmotivations behind the development of the tool are presentedfirst.andP;  This is followed by a delineation of the goals derivedfrom the motivations and examination of related work.andP;  Next thedesign choices are presented and justified.andP;  This is followed by abrief description of the tool.andP;  The presentation continues with adescription of the choices made during the implementation phase.andO;Particular attention is paid to how the sequencing of workloadcomponents was achieved.andP;  The discussion of implementation isconcluded with some necessary low level details.andP;  The validationprocedures are described.andP;  Finally the operation of the tool isexplained and conclusions are given.andP;  (Reprinted by permission ofthe publisher.)andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     SimulationTeachingPrototypePerformance MeasurementTesting.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>